item.title: Remington Express 11mm Dovetail Rail Rear Sight Replacement
item.description:
11mm Dovetail rail replacement for the Remington Express air rifle's rear sight. Uses the existing holes in the receiver that the sight originally mounted with. The many holes in the mount are for scope stop pins, which are on a lot of scope mounts.

Remix of my previous Picatinny design. I wanted to try a pistol scope with a one piece mount I had.

As with the previous design, you should be able to reuse the original sight screws (though you'll still need one), and one more (M3x7 - M3x10). It's worth noting that the original M3 screwheads are a bit weak and might strip if you aren't careful.

One problem with break barrel air rifles (and other break actions in general) is that the barrel will always lock in a slightly different position. As such, the point of impact may be different between each projectile fired when using a scope mounted on the receiver. This isn't a big problem on every break barrel airgun, but I found the variance shooting the Remington Express could be quite annoying. With something like a zero parallax reflex sight or airgun rated pistol scope, it could be useful.

Overall this design isn't as good as the picatinny design. It has to be longer, and therefore is much more wobbly than the previous design.

item.title: Quartz Game Battery Door
item.description:
This is a simple battery door replacement of the famous Submarine Quartz Game from my childhood.
Probably most of us lost this part or too damaged to operate by the usage.
I made a simple replacement for it in Tinkercad, probably can be used for similar form factor handheld machines.

Made this new one with a 2,30 mm wide groove in it to make it easier to open with wider coins.

The dimensions are as on the attached image:
Outer diameter: 16,0 mm
Inner diameter with fastener clamps: 13,7 mm
Inner diameter without fastener clamps: 11,8 mm
Height: 3,4 mm

If it doesn't fit exactly, feels loose, feel free to print by a 101 or 102% scale.

This is my first Tinkercad creation.

Share, if you like it! Thank you!

item.title: Ultimate Pokedex
item.description:
I reused the idea from brimstone326, see the original thing here: https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:4725342

I like the idea my kid can insert a Pokemon card inside the Pokedex so I just extend it about some other features and the Pokedex is a little bit bigger than the original from brimstone326.

I just redesign a little bit the cardholder with the display. In my version, the whole display part is inside the Pokedex body so it is easy to glue everything together without the gaps on the side.

Also many parts are separate from the body so it is up to you what colors will be used for display frame, buttons, etc.

Also I add some new features like:

  • card holder for up to 10 cards
  • pokeball on the cover
  • kid's name on the back (just for my personal version)

The main Pokedex body contains placeholders for all items so it is easy to glue all items in the right position.

I used the flexible glue to glue everything together.

Almost all parts are printed with resolution 0.2mm with 'ironing' option to have smooth top layers. Just the 'left' side needs to be print with supports.

I attach also PDF files with desription of all items and with labels, you can just print it out. For labels I used classic photo paper and double side tape. Photo paper is coved by classic transparent tape to protect the paper a little bit.

If you want to desing your own buttons please visit this site where you can download small icons of any Pokemon you want with transparent background: https://pokemondb.net/evolution

Hope you will enjoy and let's catch some Pokemons.

item.title: Split Tray for Galaxy Trucker 2021 Insert
item.description:
The set of inserts for the 2021 edition of Galaxy Trucker designed by Northernmenace located here is great.

https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:5002715

However, the top tray for holding the tiles, boards and manuals is quite large and won't fit my printer. I made a split tray design to replace the large tray in his insert. The inner edge is lower so it will hold the tiles but allow room for the longer boards and manuals to sit on top above the inner lip. See the photos.

Print two copies of the tray and place them with the lower edges aligned in the center. It works well for me. Thanks, Northernmenace, for such a great overall insert.

item.title: FETtec (KISS) Babytooth canopy nano camera
item.description:
Hej,

I have designed a 3,5" toothpick frame for the FETtec 15A AIO board. The frame can take actually both normal whoop AIO boards on 25,5 x 25,5 mm mounting pattern.

If you decide to build with the FETtec board the normal whoop orientation camera mounts or canopies probably will not work due to the 45-degrees angle difference.

Here comes my canopy into the picture. It can mounted on top of the FETtec AIO board similarly as you would do on normal toothpicks with the BeeBrain v2 canopy or other products.

I have made the mount for 14 mm nano cameras, with large lenses. So cameras like (and not exclusive to below list):

  • RunCam Racer Nano series
  • RunCam Nano 4
  • Foxeer Toothless 2 Nano (and Starlight Nano)
  • Caddx Ant Lite FPV Cycle Edition

item.title: MST RMX 2.0 Lambo high motor mount cover
item.description:
This is for the MST RMX 2.0 with the lambo body. Doing the high motor mount forces you to raise the body or cut a hole. This fake motor cover will make for a nice addition along with cover the hole you have to cut and keep your body nice and low.

The template is just to keep you from cutting to much of a hole. (will need to trim a little more then the temple outline. more or less just a starting point.) I did my measurements from the inside of the body. Turbos facing the rear i put the temple about 3mm back from the bottom of the rear window. keep in mind this was for my body and how i have it mounted on my chassis. my best advise is to flip the motor, put the body on and then do your best to trace out where the motor sits.then go from there. Good luck!

P:S:
There are some supports i was unable to remove. They are under the intake. Instead of risking breaking something i left mine and it didn't effect the over all look.
